						protections.</div></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s160.40000728062010715"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>SEC. 15.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 16.</i></font></h3> Section 27 is added to the Government Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_2FBB4251-F430-43D9-97B3-2DD35989E61D"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">27.</h6> (a) (1) Any provision that prohibits discrimination on the basis of sex, discrimination on the basis of gender, or similar discrimination shall also be interpreted as prohibiting sex discrimination, as defined in this section.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) In case of a conflict between the provisions of this section and other provisions of this code that set forth the scope of<font color="#B30000"><strike> “sex discrimination,”</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> sex discrimination, gender discrimination, or similar discrimination,</i></font> the provisions<font color="#B30000"><strike> of this section shall prevail over provisions with a narrower scope.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
